320 g Chicken Breast Tenders
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
56 g Carrot, julienned
28 g Baby Spinach
¼ cup Basil Pesto
2 tbsp Spicy Mayo
2 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
9 g Moo Shu Spice Blend
½ tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, lightly oil the grill. While you prep, preheat the grill to medium (approx. 400°F).
Wash and dry all produce.
Cut cucumber into 1/4-inch rounds.
In a medium bowl, whisk together vinegar and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar. Season with salt and pepper.
Add cucumbers and carrots, then toss to coat. Set aside.

In a large bowl, combine Moo Shu Spice Blend and half the hoisin sauce (use all for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.
Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
To the same bowl, add chicken, then toss to coat. Then, drizzle 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil over top of coated chicken, flipping once more to coat again.
Gather chicken, buns, a clean plate and BBQ tools on a platter, then head out to grill.

Add chicken to one side of the grill. Grill for 4-6 min per side, until chicken is cooked through.**
When done, transfer chicken to the clean plate.
Meanwhile, halve buns, then add to the grill, cut-sides down. Close lid and grill for 1-2 min, until toasted.
Transfer buns to the platter.

In a small bowl, combine spicy mayo and basil pesto.
Spread spicy basil mayo on cut-sides of buns.
Stack chicken and some marinated veggies on bottom buns. Close with top buns.
To the bowl with remaining marinated veggies, add spinach and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.
Divide sandwiches and salad between plates.